body: "Maintainer decision 2026-07-10 (review #45 follow-up): after untracking the vendored dist (pm-sod3), the end state is TypeScript-source installs — the pm CLI already loads .ts extension entries via Node native type stripping (pm-2p7a), and every first-party packages/pm-* extension is TS-only, so external flagship packages should match.\n\n## Scope (external repo unbraind/pm-changelog + a small verification here)\n1. Publish .ts source in the npm files allowlist; point manifest entry at the .ts module.\n2. Keep or drop the compiled dist during a transition window (decide in the package repo; pm_min_version must gate .ts-only tarballs to CLI versions with the native loader).\n3. In this repo: changelog:pm/check flows re-verified against a TS-entry install; sandbox packed-tarball proof in a CJS host per the P0 install lesson.\n\n## Duplicate evidence\nNo open item owns TS-source publishing for pm-changelog (searches: pm-changelog typescript source publish / vendored extension dist tracked git / managed extensions gitignore install churn). pm-2p7a (closed) shipped the loader capability only; pm-sod3 (closed) removed the vendored dist from git; this item owns the TS-only install end state."
